barrier_inperson: In-person instruction is currently being offered for students in grades K through 5th.  A total of 104 students are participating in a hybrid program. This number has increased since the previous report. The families of 36 students in grades K through 5th chose not to participate in our on-campus program and decided to continue 100% distance learning. We brought our kindergarten class back on November 9, 2020. Plans to bring in more classes were halted due to a surge in COVID-19 cases. In February, we started gradually on-boarding other classes in order to follow safety protocols. Currently, six classes/grades are operating with a hybrid schedule in order to accommodate safety protocols and families who are choosing to continue distance learning for various reasons. All families with children in grades K through 5th were given the option to participate in our hybrid program or remain in our distance learning only program. Our middle school students/teachers in grades 6th, 7th and 8th operate as a team. This presents a greater challenge with providing in-school learning with the current CDPH guidelines. There are no plans for the return of middle school students this school year.

barrier_notes:
In addition, the majority of our classrooms do not have windows that open, and we are limited to MERV 11 filters for our HVAC.
Also, about 25% of our grade 7-12 student body is not in the Irvine area, or in the same time zone. They would not be able to come for in-person instruction. Offering in person instruction means that teachers would have students for each class in one of three situations: in person, online, or overseas.
barrier_inperson:
In three surveys this year, with the most recent in March 2021, the majority of our families in grades 7-12 prefer to remain distance through the end of the year.
In two faculty and staff surveys, the majority prefer to continue with distance learning through the end of the year.
We are a small school in one building, and our community has opted for a cautious approach for our older (grade 7-12) students.
We are reviewing plans to have grade 7-12 students opt to return to campus, but no date is set.
